entry.def: If you describe a sound as tinny, you mean that it has an irritating, high-pitched quality.

example.ex: He could hear the tinny sound of a radio playing a pop song.
example.tran: 他能听到收音机播放流行歌曲的刺耳声音。

entry.tran: 质量差的;劣质金属制成的
entry.def: If you use tinny to describe something such as a cheap car, you mean that it is made of thin metal and is of poor quality.

example.ex: It is one of the cheapest cars on the market, with tinny bodywork.
example.tran: 那是市场上最廉价的汽车之一，车身用劣质金属制成。

means.word_mean: 2. thin and metallic in sound; lacking resonance;
